    <text id="R24117776T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>W. H. C. Whiting writes from Staunton to Secretary of War Randolph in June, 1862,
                    to ask if he can put to death Union soldiers captured liberating slaves.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Hon. G. W. RANDOLPH, Secretary of War:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1862-06-17">June 17, 1862.</date>
                        <name type="place">STAUNTON, VA.,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>Am I authorized by law of Virginia or Confederate States of America to hang or
                    shoot by drum head court martial marauding parties of the enemy captured
                    kidnapping negroes? Also to put to death prisoners taken with counterfeit
                    Confederate money in their possession?</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>W. H. C. WHITING.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
